49eBLP-qUnOOMlYhpdYNF8fGyeSy1UWk6XPRVVgD85lwpmbOBdCTU9POFmW3l8A-kPEuENmTY5N1eZfpg8DtIQzKE6BFjlp94YUyYrydGEqJHOQjGvtZePEfgRhpfRtMf-o3ObesZ3J-ROakXh3Ka7lxBGmE03UKVS5rrvYPiFm1v6ZFLfPycVciMXegoWQ05G-4rs0xGCUe_b9shMoV4mhpIq8V9njBx2fECgedz5PztqBkKVT4WxZMf0N8kLT8a8r4UhmCRMb8IeAdmjW6jC1yR1yW8Ic9Hm5dX3A_1f7ev4M-4lVdnYy1m13V8oed-Hw9JR2hf-fCSPwJiaXlw4bgX64SI44oAxUrqd3xPqe_oAS6MJ8fReayrQOFcUazbi5hGq-Wrf5OrO809FZK_ss=\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring JUnit functionality**\\n\\nI'm thinking about JUnit Jupiter 5.9 and how it might discover a @Test class that has an unknown annotation. It seems possible if we define a ClassTemplate annotation from API 5.13. I wonder if the engine can execute a class with a @Test method and report the ClassSource. It’s interesting that the scanner identifies the @ClassTemplate annotation by name and expands upon it. There’s a lot to consider here!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Considering JUnit implementation**\\n\\nI’m thinking about how to set up the class template correctly. I can add `testImplementation \\\"org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-api:5.13.0\\\"` just for the annotation. But there’s a potential issue if the compile selects the 5.13 API over 5.9—how well will the runtime handle that? Usually, platforms align, but mixing versions might lead to incompatibility. It could be simpler to just stick with `5.13.0` for the API, even though the engine is using the older version. The `@ClassTemplate` might be considered experimental since 5.13, but it should work well.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Examining Spring and JUnit compatibility**\\n\\nI noticed that the test class runs normally thanks to the `@Test` method, and the SpringExtension can load the context just fine. However, there's a potential issue with `@ClassTemplate` if it’s meta-annotated `@Testable`, as the 5.9 engine might overlook that. Adding a dependency version could help. I wonder if `@Nested` exists in 5.9, which could lead to conflicts with the build's JUnit API. I’ll simplify the structure with a static nested class for the test case, but I need to confirm how the nested class handles extension inheritance.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_ikcrAVlAqyI9BruMxjnVehpn|fc_0ae776a84db08a08016a293485a4388194ad78fb7358e7e365", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/build.gradle", "edits": [{"oldText": "    testImplementation \"org.springframework:spring-context:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'junit:junit:4.13.2'\n", "newText": "    testImplementation \"org.springframework:spring-context:$libraryVersion\"\n    testImplementation 'org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-api:5.13.0'\n    testImplementation 'junit:junit:4.13.2'\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 3771, "output": 2456, "cacheRead": 29696, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 35923, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781085265239, "responseId": "resp_0ae776a84db08a08016a293451b010819493d82d6d5c802d10"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_ikcrAVlAqyI9BruMxjnVehpn|fc_0ae776a84db08a08016a293485a4388194ad78fb7358e7e365", "toolName": "edit", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully replaced 1 block(s) in tests/src/org.springframework/spring-test/7.0.0/build.gradle."}], "details": {"diff": "    ...\n 12 \n 13 dependencies {\n 14     testImplementation \"org.springframework:spring-test:$libraryVersion\"\n 15     testImplementation \"org.springframework:spring-context:$libraryVersion\"\n+16     testImplementation 'org.junit.jupiter:junit-jupiter-api:5.13.0'\n 16     testImplementation 'junit:junit:4.13.2'\n 17     testImplementation 'commons-logging:commons-logging:1.1.1'\n 18     testImplementation 'org.assertj:assertj-core:3.22.0'\n 19 }\n    ...", "firstChangedLine": 16}, "isError": false, "timestamp"